{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:ephesians.5",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "ephesians",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Ephesians 5 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:1",
      "text": "Be therefore imitators of God, as beloved children.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:2",
      "text": "Walk in love, even as Christ also loved us and gave himself up for us, an offering and a sacrifice to God for a sweet-smelling fragrance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:3",
      "text": "But sexual immorality, and all uncleanness or covetousness, let it not even be mentioned among you, as becomes saints;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:4",
      "text": "nor filthiness, nor foolish talking, nor jesting, which are not appropriate, but rather giving of thanks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:5",
      "text": "Know this for sure, that no sexually immoral person, nor unclean person, nor covetous man (who is an idolater), has any inheritance in the Kingdom of Christ and God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:6",
      "text": "Let no one deceive you with empty words, for because of these things the wrath of God comes on the children of disobedience.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:7",
      "text": "Therefore don’t be partakers with them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:8",
      "text": "For you were once darkness, but are now light in the Lord. Walk as children of light,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:9",
      "text": "for the fruit of the Spirit is in all goodness and righteousness and truth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:10",
      "text": "proving what is well pleasing to the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:11",
      "text": "Have no fellowship with the unfruitful deeds of darkness, but rather even reprove them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:12",
      "text": "For it is a shame even to speak of the things which are done by them in secret.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:13",
      "text": "But all things, when they are reproved, are revealed by the light, for everything that reveals is light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:14",
      "text": "Therefore he says, “ Awake, you who sleep, and arise from the dead, and Christ will shine on you.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:15",
      "text": "Therefore watch carefully how you walk, not as unwise, but as wise,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:16",
      "text": "redeeming the time, because the days are evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:17",
      "text": "Therefore, don’ t be foolish, but understand what the will of the Lord is.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:18",
      "text": "Don’t be drunken with wine, in which is dissipation, but be filled with the Spirit,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:19",
      "text": "speaking to one another in psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs; singing and making melody in your heart to the Lord;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:20",
      "text": "giving thanks always concerning all things in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ to God, even the Father;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:21",
      "text": "subjecting yourselves to one another in the fear of Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:22",
      "text": "Wives, be subject to your own husbands, as to the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:23",
      "text": "For the husband is the head of the wife, as Christ also is the head of the assembly, being himself the savior of the body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:24",
      "text": "But as the assembly is subject to Christ, so let the wives also be to their own husbands in everything.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:25",
      "text": "Husbands, love your wives, even as Christ also loved the assembly and gave himself up for her,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:26",
      "text": "that he might sanctify her, having cleansed her by the washing of water with the word,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:27",
      "text": "that he might present the assembly to himself gloriously, not having spot or wrinkle or any such thing, but that she should be holy and without defect.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:28",
      "text": "Even so husbands also ought to love their own wives as their own bodies. He who loves his own wife loves himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:29",
      "text": "For no man ever hated his own flesh, but nourishes and cherishes it, even as the Lord also does the assembly,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:30",
      "text": "because we are members of his body, of his flesh and bones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:31",
      "text": "“ For this cause a man will leave his father and mother and will be joined to his wife. Then the two will become one flesh.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:32",
      "text": "This mystery is great, but I speak concerning Christ and the assembly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ephesians.5.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:33",
      "text": "Nevertheless each of you must also love his own wife even as himself; and let the wife see that she respects her husband.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
